18/20) @eBay COMPLETELY ignored all the facts and refused to take the time or effort to help my boyfriend save his business. But why would they care in the first place? They've already replaced all the small business owners and sellers with corporate name-brand companies anywayü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

17/20) Today he decides he's finally going to call @eBay and find out what the hell is going on. @eBay told him they never got the documents he sent, and that the decision to PERMANENTLY ban his account is FINAL. So much for the appeals department huh.

16/20) He waits DAYS, but he still never gets any confirmation about @eBay receiving the documents. Someone was also supposed to call him to update him on the appeal process, but again, no one ever called him back.

15/20) @eBay 's appeal person told my boyfriend that all he needed to do was submit the court documents regarding the person who stole his packages and anything else that might help. He did. He never got the confirmation email that said @eBay  received the documents.

14/20) He gave up on @eBay for a few days, but then he decided he'd fight for his business. The first person he spoke to from @eBay HUNG UP ON HIM. After waiting for HOURS, he was finally able to get a hold of the appeals department, which tbh should've been done a long time ago.

13/20) @eBay straight up said "It doesn't matter, you made a new account while you already had a restricted one. You broke our terms, you're permanently banned from using our site. End of story." Suuuuper seller friendly right?

12/20) He finally gets on the phone with @eBay and explains to them the situation. He tells them that he didn't know his old account was still up, and that even though it was restricted, it was due to someone stealing from him.

11/20) He calls @eBay , trying to figure out what happened. Last time he checked, that old account was closed, but as you and I know, it wasn't. My boyfriend's business is at risk of going under and he could lose EVERYTHING.

10/20) It goes well for a few weeks, money is flowing and he's getting nothing but great reviews. Well, two weeks ago he gets an email from @eBay saying that his account has been banned INDEFINITELY because they linked his information to his old restricted account.

9/20) Fast forward to the present: years have passed and my boyfriend had forgotten about his old @eBay account. He actually thought it had been closed. So, he decides to open a new account for his new small business, again, because his friends were making good money on there.

8/20) The logical thing to do would be to close the @eBay account and make a new one right? Wrong. If your account is restricted, you're not allowed to close it. This is another system that protects buyers from scammers, but in this case it made my boyfriend's life even harder.

7/20) The only way to get your @eBay account unrestricted is to have a streak of positive reviews, but with all the comments under his store complaining about not receiving items, there was no way of GETTING positive reviews because no one wanted to take the "risk."
6/20) My boyfriend had hundreds of dollars worth of product stolen from him, and the reputation of his @eBay store was now affected because of something out of his control. And @eBay didn't care!

5/20) After communicating with @eBay about what happened and presenting them with the court documents, eBay straight up said "We don't care if you have proof that the items you sold were stolen, the customers never received them so your account is still restricted." So logical.

4/20) @eBay has a system that restricts a seller's account if they get negative reviews or if a product they sold doesn't arrive inorder to protect the buyers from getting scammed. This is what happened to my boyfriend's account.

3/20) That person was eventually caught and charged with a federal crime for stealing mail, but because the packages they stole from my boyfriend never arrived to the customers, his @eBay got flooded with negative reviews.
